    <p class="text-gray-700">The most common mistake is buying old vintages or wines that have been stored improperly, as Sauvignon Blanc is particularly sensitive to light and heat exposure. Many consumers also overlook the harvest date, choosing bottles that are 3+ years old when fresher alternatives are available. Additionally, people often expect all Sauvignon Blancs to taste the same, missing out on the distinct terroir expressions from different regions—Loire Valley's minerality versus Marlborough's tropical intensity.</p>
